'''Paul-Louis Roubert''' (born 1967) is an associate researcher at the ''Laboratoire d'histoire visuelle contemporaine'', senior lecturer in photography at [[Paris 8 University]] and, since December 2010, president of the [[Soci<U+00E9>t<U+00E9> fran<U+00E7>aise de photographie]].<ref name=culturevisuelle>[http://culturevisuelle.org/blog/7296 Michel Poivert, "Paul-Louis Roubert nouveau pr<U+00E9>sident de la SFP"], ''Culture visuelle''. {{Fr icon}} Retrieved 3 March 2011.</ref><ref name=lhivic>[http://www.arhv.lhivic.org/index.php/2007/06/12/431-paul-louis-roubert-elu-maitre-de-conferences-a-paris-8 Andr<U+00E9> Gunthert, "Paul-Louis Roubert <U+00E9>lu ma<U+00EE>tre de conf<U+00E9>rences <U+00E0> Paris 8"], Actualit<U+00E9>s de la Recherche en histoire visuelle. {{Fr icon}} Retrieved 3 March 2011.</ref> 

Roubert was awarded a doctorate in 2004 on the basis of his thesis on ''L'Introduction du mod<U+00E8>le photographique dans la critique d'art en France'' which led to ''L'Image sans qualit<U+00E9>s'' published in 2006. He has been closely connected to the Soci<U+00E9>t<U+00E9> fran<U+00E7>aise de photographie whose bulletin he edited from 1999 to 2004. Since 1996, He has been a founding member of the journal ''Etudes photographiques''. He has lectured in the history of photography at Paris 8, Paris 1 and at the [[<U+00C9>cole des hautes <U+00E9>tudes en sciences sociales]]. In December 2010, he was unanimously elected president of the Soci<U+00E9>t<U+00E9> fran<U+00E7>aise de photographie.<ref name=culturevisuelle/><ref name=lhivic/> 

==Main publications==

*"L'Image sans qualit<U+00E9>s". Les beaux-arts et la critique <U+00E0> l'<U+00E9>preuve de la photographie, 1839-1859, Paris, Monum, 2006. 
*"Le daguerr<U+00E9>otype en proc<U+00E8>s", Le Daguerr<U+00E9>otype fran<U+00E7>ais. Un objet photographique (cat. exp.), Paris, Mus<U+00E9>e d<U+2019>Orsay/RMN, 2003, p. 119-131. 
*"1859. Exposer la photographie", <U+00C9>tudes photographiques.

